instructions:
## Set up Recharts in Next.js / React

### 1. Install Recharts
- Run: `npm install recharts`.
- Recharts is a composable charting library built on React and D3. It requires React 18+.
- No peer dependency issues with Next.js App Router.

### 2. Important: Client Components only
- Recharts components use browser APIs and cannot render in React Server Components.
- All chart components must be in a file with `'use client';` at the top.
- Create a wrapper component and import it in your Server Component pages.

### 3. Responsive container (required)
- Always wrap every chart in `<ResponsiveContainer>` so it fills its parent:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { ResponsiveContainer, BarChart, Bar, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, Legend } from 'recharts';
  const data = [
    { month: 'Jan', revenue: 4000, users: 240 },
    { month: 'Feb', revenue: 3000, users: 139 },
    { month: 'Mar', revenue: 5000, users: 380 },
  ];
  export function RevenueBarChart() {
    return (
      <div className="h-64 w-full">
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
          <BarChart data={data} margin={{ top: 5, right: 20, left: 0, bottom: 5 }}>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
            <XAxis dataKey="month" />
            <YAxis />
            <Tooltip />
            <Legend />
            <Bar dataKey="revenue" fill="#6366f1" radius={[4, 4, 0, 0]} />
            <Bar dataKey="users" fill="#22c55e" radius={[4, 4, 0, 0]} />
          </BarChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
- Set an explicit height on the parent `<div>` — `ResponsiveContainer` with `height="100%"` reads the parent's height. Without a fixed parent height, the chart collapses to 0.

### 4. Line chart
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { ResponsiveContainer, LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, Legend } from 'recharts';
  export function UserGrowthChart({ data }: { data: { date: string; users: number }[] }) {
    return (
      <div className="h-64 w-full">
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
          <LineChart data={data}>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" stroke="#e5e7eb" />
            <XAxis dataKey="date" tick={{ fontSize: 12 }} />
            <YAxis tick={{ fontSize: 12 }} />
            <Tooltip />
            <Legend />
            <Line
              type="monotone"
              dataKey="users"
              stroke="#6366f1"
              strokeWidth={2}
              dot={false}
              activeDot={{ r: 4 }}
            />
          </LineChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```

### 5. Area chart
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { ResponsiveContainer, AreaChart, Area, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip } from 'recharts';
  export function RevenueAreaChart({ data }: { data: { month: string; revenue: number }[] }) {
    return (
      <div className="h-64 w-full">
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
          <AreaChart data={data}>
            <defs>
              <linearGradient id="revenueGradient" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
                <stop offset="5%" stopColor="#6366f1" stopOpacity={0.3} />
                <stop offset="95%" stopColor="#6366f1" stopOpacity={0} />
              </linearGradient>
            </defs>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
            <XAxis dataKey="month" />
            <YAxis />
            <Tooltip />
            <Area
              type="monotone"
              dataKey="revenue"
              stroke="#6366f1"
              strokeWidth={2}
              fill="url(#revenueGradient)"
            />
          </AreaChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```

### 6. Pie chart
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { ResponsiveContainer, PieChart, Pie, Cell, Tooltip, Legend } from 'recharts';
  const COLORS = ['#6366f1', '#22c55e', '#f59e0b', '#ef4444', '#3b82f6'];
  export function CategoryPieChart({ data }: { data: { name: string; value: number }[] }) {
    return (
      <div className="h-64 w-full">
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
          <PieChart>
            <Pie
              data={data}
              cx="50%"
              cy="50%"
              outerRadius={80}
              dataKey="value"
              label={({ name, percent }) => `${name} ${(percent * 100).toFixed(0)}%`}
            >
              {data.map((_, index) => (
                <Cell key={`cell-${index}`} fill={COLORS[index % COLORS.length]} />
              ))}
            </Pie>
            <Tooltip />
            <Legend />
          </PieChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```

### 7. Custom tooltip
- Replace the default tooltip with a branded one:
  ```tsx
  import type { TooltipProps } from 'recharts';
  function CustomTooltip({ active, payload, label }: TooltipProps<number, string>) {
    if (!active || !payload?.length) return null;
    return (
      <div className="rounded-lg border bg-background p-3 shadow-md text-sm">
        <p className="font-medium mb-1">{label}</p>
        {payload.map((entry) => (
          <p key={entry.dataKey} style={{ color: entry.color }}>
            {entry.name}: {entry.value?.toLocaleString()}
          </p>
        ))}
      </div>
    );
  }
  // Usage: <Tooltip content={<CustomTooltip />} />
  ```

### 8. Dark mode support
- Pass stroke colors via CSS variables or conditionally based on `resolvedTheme` from next-themes:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { useTheme } from 'next-themes';
  export function ThemedChart({ data }) {
    const { resolvedTheme } = useTheme();
    const gridColor = resolvedTheme === 'dark' ? '#374151' : '#e5e7eb';
    const textColor = resolvedTheme === 'dark' ? '#9ca3af' : '#6b7280';
    return (
      <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
        <LineChart data={data}>
          <CartesianGrid stroke={gridColor} />
          <XAxis tick={{ fill: textColor }} />
          <YAxis tick={{ fill: textColor }} />
          <Tooltip contentStyle={{ backgroundColor: resolvedTheme === 'dark' ? '#1f2937' : '#ffffff' }} />
          <Line dataKey="value" stroke="#6366f1" />
        </LineChart>
      </ResponsiveContainer>
    );
  }
  ```

### 9. Formatting axis values
- Format large numbers on the Y axis:
  ```tsx
  const formatYAxis = (value: number) => {
    if (value >= 1_000_000) return `${(value / 1_000_000).toFixed(1)}M`;
    if (value >= 1_000) return `${(value / 1_000).toFixed(0)}k`;
    return String(value);
  };
  // Usage: <YAxis tickFormatter={formatYAxis} />
  ```

### 10. Verify the chart renders
- Run `npm run dev` and navigate to the page with the chart.
- Resize the browser window to confirm the chart is responsive.
- Open DevTools → Console and confirm there are no `Warning: Each child in a list` or `Invalid prop` errors.
- If the chart area is blank, check the parent container has an explicit height set.

### Common errors & fixes
- **Chart area is blank / zero height** — `ResponsiveContainer` reads the parent's height. Add an explicit `h-48` or `h-64` class (or inline `style={{ height: '256px' }}`) to the wrapper `<div>`.
- **'useTheme must be used within ThemeProvider'** — You added theme-aware colors but haven't set up next-themes. Either add the ThemeProvider or use hard-coded colors.
- **Text not exported from recharts** — You are trying to import `Text` directly. Use `<text>` (SVG element) or recharts' `Label` component inside chart elements instead.
- **Tooltip shows undefined** — The `dataKey` in `<Bar>` / `<Line>` must exactly match the property name in your data objects (case-sensitive).
- **Chart renders in SSR and throws** — You forgot `'use client'` at the top of the file. Recharts components are client-only.
- **Legend labels showing 'dataKey' instead of names** — Pass `name` prop to `<Bar>`, `<Line>`, or `<Area>`: `<Bar dataKey="revenue" name="Revenue" />`.
- **PieChart label overlaps** — Use `labelLine={false}` and custom outer labels, or use a `<Legend>` instead of inline labels.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT use Recharts in Server Components — every component that imports from `recharts` must have `'use client'`.
- Do NOT omit `<ResponsiveContainer>` — charts without it have a fixed width and won't be responsive on mobile.
- Do NOT set the height on `ResponsiveContainer` itself without also giving its parent a height — `height="100%"` on the container only works if the parent has a defined height.
- Do NOT pass non-numeric data directly to `dataKey` — pre-transform your data to numbers before passing to chart components.
- Do NOT use inline styles for chart dimensions in production — set them via Tailwind or CSS classes on the wrapper div for maintainability.
- Do NOT build custom SVG-based charts from scratch when Recharts provides the chart type — this adds complexity for no benefit.
